parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rust and corrosion of the frame can lead to structural failure, compromising the vehicle's safety and potentially causing accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Rust holes in the frame
warped frame
loud rattling noise under the passenger side steer tire
difficulty controlling the steering
bouncing when hitting bumps
excessive rust throughout the frame and suspension.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the suspension can lead to loss of control, accidents, or injuries.
symptoms: Broken leaf spring
rusted leaf spring
rear universal joint failure
front driver-side tire component failure
squeaky rear springs.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unavailability of parts for recall repairs can lead to delays and inconvenience, potentially causing safety risks if the issues are not addressed promptly.
symptoms: Parts not available for recall repairs
dealerships not performing recall repairs
manufacturers not providing adequate support for recall repairs.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended acceleration of the vehicle can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates without warning
even when the brake pedal is depressed
and may continue to accelerate even after the accelerator pedal is released. The vehicle may also surge forward or backward
and the engine RPM may increase excessively.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A sticking accelerator pedal can cause the vehicle to accelerate unintentionally, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The accelerator pedal becomes stuck or wedged
causing the vehicle to accelerate unexpectedly
and may require excessive force to release.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Problems with the brake pedal can cause the vehicle to accelerate unintentionally, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal may feel soft or spongy
or may not respond properly
causing the vehicle to accelerate or fail to slow down as expected.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion and rust of the frame can cause the vehicle to become unsafe to operate, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. In severe cases, the frame can collapse, causing the vehicle to break in half.
symptoms: Rust or corrosion on the frame
holes in the frame
cracking or breaking of the frame
abnormal noises or vibrations while driving
difficulty steering or controlling the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Failure due to Frame Corrosion
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brakes due to frame corrosion can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Sudden loss of brake function
soft or spongy brake pedal
difficulty stopping the vehicle
unusual noises or vibrations while braking.
